{{Quote|I found it years ago. When I was no older than you are now. I found it in the River of Light on my home planet.|Qui-Gon Jinn, handing Obi-Wan Kenobi a stone from the River of Light|<ref name="THP" />}}
The '''River of Light''' was located on the [[Qui-Gon Jinn's homeworld|homeworld]] of [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Qui-Gon Jinn/Legends|Qui-Gon Jinn]]. While there, a thirteen-[[Standard year/Legends|year]]-old Jinn obtained a [[Force-sensitive stone]] that he kept as a memento for over three [[Time/Legends|decades]].<ref name="THP" /> In [[44 BBY/Legends|44 BBY]],<ref name="44 BBY">According to ''[[The Essential Reader's Companion]]'' the events of ''[[Jedi Apprentice: The Hidden Past]]'' take place in 44 BBY.</ref> he gave [[River stone|the stone]] to his [[Padawan/Legends|Padawan]] [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] as a gift for his thirteenth [[Birthday/Legends|birthday]].<ref name="THP" /> Kenobi in turn gave the same stone to his apprentice [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] when he turned thirteen<ref name="TOTJ">''[[Jedi Quest: The Way of the Apprentice]]''</ref> in [[28 BBY/Legends|28 BBY]].<ref name="28 BBY">According to [[Leland Chee]] ({{Blog|holocron|13/comments|Major Character Birth Years}}), Anakin Skywalker was born in 41.9 BBY; therefore his thirteenth birthday can be placed at 28.9 BBY.</ref> Knowledge of the [[Force-sensitive/Legends|Force-sensitive]] river stones' existence survived into the [[Standard day/Legends|days]] of the [[New Jedi Order]];<ref name="Droids">{{Hyperspace|url=hyperspace/member/insideronline/81/indexp7.html|text=Droids, Technology and the Force: A Clash of Phenomena|int=Droids, Technology and the Force: A Clash of Phenomena (article)}}</ref> following the [[Battle of Yuuzhan'tar|end]] of the [[Yuuzhan Vong War]] in [[29 ABY/Legends|29 ABY]],<ref name="29 ABY">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' {{C|The Recapture of Coruscant (29 A.B.Y.)}}</ref> [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]] [[Tam Azur-Jamin]] mentioned them in ''[[Droids, Technology and the Force: A Clash of Phenomena]]'', an essay discussing the emergence of the Force in inanimate objects and technological devices.<ref name="Droids" />

==Behind the scenes==
Created by author [[Jude Watson]], the River of Light was first mentioned in [[Jedi Apprentice: The Hidden Past|''The Hidden Past'']] ([[1999]]), the third installment in the [[Star Wars: Jedi Apprentice|''Jedi Apprentice'']] series of young reader novels.<ref name="THP" /> [[Droids, Technology and the Force: A Clash of Phenomena (article)|''Droids, Technology and the Force: A Clash of Phenomena'']], a [[2005]] [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|Hyperspace]]-exclusive article by [[Abel G. Peña]], mentions the Force being found in "lifeless rocks like river stones."<ref name="Droids" /> In the article endnotes published at his [[StarWars.com]] blog, Peña specified that this was meant as a reference to the stones found on Qui-Gon Jinn's homeworld,<ref name="Blog">{{Blog|abelgpena|47|Endnotes for ''Droids, Technology and the Force: A Clash of Phenomena, Part I''}}</ref> thus making the article's reference to "river" an indirect mention of the River of Light.

